The Head of Service (HOS) of the Federation, Dr Folasade Yemi -Esan has directed officers on Grade Level 14 and above including those on essential services to resume work with effect from Monday, 4th May, 2020. A press statement signed by the Director, Information, Office of the Head of the Civil Service of the Federation, Mrs. Olawunmi Ogunmosunle revealed that the directive is in furtherance to President Muhammadu Buhari’s broadcast on a phased and gradual easing of the lockdown measures occasioned by COVID-19. The Head of Service in her statement also issued the following directives; “Offices are to open Three (3) times a week, namely Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. The closing time shall be 2.00pm on each day”. “The concerned officers are to ensure full compliance with the directives and advice on the prevention of the COVID -19 pandemic. These measures include maintenance of social distancing, regular washing and /or sanitizing of hands and wearing of face masks”, she said. While instructing that officers should ensure that they don’t receive large number of visitors to their places of work, Yemi-Esan also directed that they should ensure that the visitors comply with safety and health advices/ directives. She also advised the Permanent Secretaries and Chief Executive Officers to ensure that hand washing and sanitation facilities are placed at entrances and strategic points in their MDAs and urged them to ensure that Infrared thermometers are provided at the entrance of the MDAs for compulsory temperature checks. Meanwhile, the Federal Secretariat Complexes have been decontaminated while efforts are ongoing to do same in other public offices.